NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Because Jenny has 5 spades (at least) and I have 4 spades, I know we have a 9-card fit, so 3@S is the bid based on the Law of Total Tricks. And that is always the best guideline to use. I would expect most of my students to bid 3@S and that would be fine. I am just explaining some tactical considerations as to why you might consider 2@S or 4@S. |
