mb|4S|NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|That says I might bid 4@S right away just to make it harder for the opps to figure out what to do As a general rule, if you have at least 9 spades, and they bid 4@H, you should almost always bid 4@S. Some experts say that "4@S is automatic" in that situation. I also might bid 2@S, hoping that they have a game but wont bid it, because if West bids 3@H, East might not bid 4@H|
PG| ***** 54 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|2@S is not likely to work out particularly well, especially if we can make 3@S and I pass 3@H (which is what I would do if I only bid 2@S). I have to be consistent. If I bid 2@S, I would do so hoping to talk them out of 4@H, so bidding 2@S then 3@S makes no sense whatsoever. So because I have a singleton heart, and we are not vul, I am going to bid 4@S and hope that it is right. At the very least, it will give the opps a big problem but as I said, the technically correct bid is 3@S. 4@S is more of a tactical bid.|
