^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Okay bidding so far other than Jenny should have opened 2@H. As to Don's 3@S bid. So long as you have the agreement that it simply shows 4-card spade support and does not promise any points (which is what I play) he can bid 3@S. That it is a LOTT bid but it would also be reasonable to play that you don't make an LOTT bid unless you have at least 6 points (or you are jumping to 4. However, I play the way Don bid it, that 3@S simply shows 4 spades and can be done with very few HCP.|
